[I🔥 Level 1 – Timer as a Pure Time Base (Update Event Mastery)
Task 1: 1ms Heartbeat Using General Timer (NOT SysTick)

Do not use SysTick. Disable HAL time base if needed.

Configure a general-purpose timer (like TIM2 or TIM3) to generate an update interrupt every 1 ms.

Inside the ISR:

Increment a volatile uint32_t ms_counter.

In main():

Every 1000 ms, toggle an LED.

Every 5000 ms, print something via UART (but NOT inside ISR).

What this forces you to understand:

Prescaler calculation

ARR calculation

Update interrupt enable

Clearing UIF flag

Why volatile matters

Keeping ISR short

Software time tracking

If your LED drifts → your math is wrong.